<TITLE> Debashish Roy's mother admitted to LadAid hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 19 (bdnews24.com)Rani Aroti Roy, mother of the chief adviser's special assistant in charge of CHT affairs Raja Debashish Roy, has been admitted to LabAid Cardiac Hospital in the city. "My mother was admitted to LabAid hospital Friday night as she has heart disease and was suffering chest pains" Debashish told bdnews24.com Saturday evening. On the condition of his mother, the special aide said doctors had yet to inform him of anything definite. "The doctors will let us know about her condition on Tuesday after all the required tests have been done." LabAid hospital spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com Debashish Roy's mother Aroti Roy was admitted Friday. She is now being treated by a five-member medical board under the supervision of Dr Baren Chakravarty at the hospital's Coronary Care Unit, Azad said. bdnews
